T1  - Note: Institutional Distance and The Multinational Enterprise
AU  - Xu, Dean
AU  - Shenkar, Oded
Y1  - 2002/10/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2002.7566108
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2002.7566108
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 608
EP  - 618
VL  - 27
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We draw from the recently developed construct of institutional distance to propose a framework that explains foreign direct investment by the multinational enterprise. We decompose the institutional distance between the host and home countries into distances on the regulative, normative, and cognitive dimensions of institutions, and match these with firm-level attributes to produce propositions regarding host country selection and foreign market entry strategies.
AB  - We draw from the recently developed construct of institutional distance to propose a framework that explains foreign direct investment by the multinational enterprise. We decompose the institutional distance between the host and home countries into distances on the regulative, normative, and cognitive dimensions of institutions, and match these with firm-level attributes to produce propositions regarding host country selection and foreign market entry strategies.
